Text.Value: *You think of adventurers giving themselves to oblexes. Sharran priests offering oblivion to grievers. Criminals seeking true deniability from hags.*
*No tales of wilfully surrendering memory come to mind.*
*This is Sharran work. Clean. Untraceable. Not the hack-job of Father Bhaal.
Now, it was a pleasure talking with you, but I really should be getting on. Shouldn't I? Yes, I think so...

EditorData.NodeContext: befuddled, has had his memory wiped

Text.Value: I don't remember, do I? But it must have been a very good reason. Otherwise, why would I've done it? Right?
Messed up is what I was before! I was a playwright who'd lost the will to create. Now I see just how little that matters.
*Priests serving the Raven Queen, the Nightbringer, and He of the Third Eye all offer oblivion to those who seek it.*
*Wherever hardship walks, a willingness to forget does not trail far behind.*
Well, all my memories, actually.
How did they do that?
Hello again, travellers! Now that I'm a new man, I feel warm benevolence towards all humanity!
*To willingly annihilate a part of one's memory, their identity, their very soul - few priests would sanction such an act.*
It was called the Unburdening, I know that! As for anything else about it, I can't remember. Of course.
Hail, friend that I definitely remember! What happened to you?
Hello, old friend! Or so I assume. I used to know everybody around town, but now I'm a new man.
I'm not sure. How would I know? Anyway, now I'm relearning what wine tastes like, and it's delightful!
Why? You coward. What I wouldn't give to get my mind back.
Leave.
A simple procedure at the House of Grief, and my worries were gone! They removed my bad memories.
A new man? Who were you when you were an old man?
Wonder if this procedure happened to you.
A curious 'procedure' - consider what priests might offer that treatment.
You sound kind of messed up, to be honest.
All your memories? Don't you miss some of them?
A worried man, a playwright who'd lost the will to write. Now I worry no more! Can't write a word? What does it matter?
Why would you let them do that?
How did you become the new man that you are now?
Leave.
How unusual - recall any tales you've heard of voluntary memory loss.
We learn from our past to forge our present - how could you erase that?

Synopsis: Speak with Oloric Witmirth, a playwright, at Elfsong Tavern. He's been through the Unburdening at the House of Grief.
